# Trivy CVE ignore list — accepted risks with documented justification.
#
# Format: CVE-ID  # justification
#
# How to add: when Trivy blocks a build on a CVE that is:
#   (a) a false positive, or
#   (b) not exploitable in our runtime configuration, or
#   (c) has no fix available and is tracked in the version registry
# Add the CVE here with a justification comment.
#
# Review cadence: quarterly. Remove entries when the CVE is patched in the base image.

# Example (uncomment and replace when needed):
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # Not exploitable: we use non-root containers and read-only root FS.
#                 # No fix available as of 2025-06-01. Tracked in 15-version-registry.html.
